abstract: The Alaska Supreme Court on Friday cleared the way for a campaign seeking to oust the state's embattled governor to proceed with plans to collect enough signatures to place a recall initiative on the 2020 ballot.
snippet: The Alaska Supreme Court on Friday cleared the way for a campaign seeking to oust the state's embattled governor to proceed with plans to collect enough signatures to place a recall initiative on the 2020 ballot.
lead_paragraph: ANCHORAGE, Alaska — The Alaska Supreme Court on Friday cleared the way for a campaign seeking to oust the state's embattled governor to proceed with plans to collect enough signatures to place a recall initiative on the 2020 ballot.
headline_main: Alaska High Court OKs Recall Petition Drive for Campaign to Oust Governor
headline_print_headline: Alaska High Court OKs Recall Petition Drive for Campaign to Oust Governor

abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Saturday, Feb. 15, 2020.
snippet: Corrections that appeared in print on Saturday, Feb. 15, 2020.
lead_paragraph: An article on Friday about Attorney General William P. Barr’s rebuke of President Trump’s attacks on the Justice Department misstated who informed Mr. Trump of what Mr. Barr planned to say in an ABC News interview. The attorney general’s office, not Mr. Barr himself, sent word to a White House official.

abstract: To keep a promise as he runs for re-election, Trump uses more military funds to pay for the border wall.
snippet: To keep a promise as he runs for re-election, Trump uses more military funds to pay for the border wall.
lead_paragraph: That “big, beautiful wall” President Trump never tires of carrying on about is becoming one of the most expensive campaign stunts ever. It is a potentially unconstitutional one as well, as the Defense Department prepares to divert more billions of dollars authorized by Congress from a variety of weapons programs to generate bragging rights for Mr. Trump’s re-election campaign.

abstract: What happens when the left cedes the free speech high ground?
snippet: What happens when the left cedes the free speech high ground?
lead_paragraph: Several months after the Harvey Weinstein scandal broke and the #MeToo movement got powerfully underway, Katie Roiphe, writing in the reliably liberal Harper’s Magazine, wrote an essay on what she called “The Other Whisper Network.” It was the sort of piece that took great honesty to write and greater courage to publish.

abstract: Amid mounting furor over politicization at the Justice Department, the attorney general ordered reviews of such investigations and prosecutions.
snippet: Amid mounting furor over politicization at the Justice Department, the attorney general ordered reviews of such investigations and prosecutions.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — While Attorney General William P. Barr asserted his independence from the White House this week, he has also been quietly intervening in a series of politically charged cases, including against Michael T. Flynn, President Trump’s former national security adviser, people familiar with the matter said on Friday.

abstract: The Trump administration announced it would increase tariffs on European aircraft in an effort to ramp up pressure in a long-running airplane subsidy dispute.
snippet: The Trump administration announced it would increase tariffs on European aircraft in an effort to ramp up pressure in a long-running airplane subsidy dispute.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration said it would raise tariffs on European aircraft in an effort to pressure Europe in a long-running trade dispute over airplane subsidies.

headline_main: Trump Administration Will Raise Tariffs on European Aircraft
headline_print_headline: In Subsidies Feud, Trump Administration Will Raise Tariffs on European Aircraft

abstract: The U.S. government on Friday said it would increase tariffs on aircraft imported from the European Union to 15% from 10%, ratcheting up pressure on Brussels in a nearly 16-year transatlantic dispute over aircraft subsidies.
snippet: The U.S. government on Friday said it would increase tariffs on aircraft imported from the European Union to 15% from 10%, ratcheting up pressure on Brussels in a nearly 16-year transatlantic dispute over aircraft subsidies.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. government on Friday said it would increase tariffs on aircraft imported from the European Union to 15% from 10%, ratcheting up pressure on Brussels in a nearly 16-year transatlantic dispute over aircraft subsidies.
headline_main: U.S. Raises Tariffs on European Aircraft in Ongoing Dispute Over Subsidies
headline_print_headline: U.S. Raises Tariffs on European Aircraft in Ongoing Dispute Over Subsidies

abstract: The U.S. Court of International Trade has issued a temporary order under which U.S. customs agents cannot collect duties from a U.S. company under President Donald Trump's recently-announced expansion of steel and aluminum tariffs.
snippet: The U.S. Court of International Trade has issued a temporary order under which U.S. customs agents cannot collect duties from a U.S. company under President Donald Trump's recently-announced expansion of steel and aluminum tariffs.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. Court of International Trade has issued a temporary order under which U.S. customs agents cannot collect duties from a U.S. company under President Donald Trump's recently-announced expansion of steel and aluminum tariffs.
headline_main: U.S. Firm Wins Reprieve From Expanded Duties on Steel Products
headline_print_headline: U.S. Firm Wins Reprieve From Expanded Duties on Steel Products

abstract: The U.S. attorney assisting in the Justice Department's review of the criminal case of former National Security Adviser Michael Flynn is an ex-FBI agent with a long background in battling white-collar crime.
